HEADWORD: Melilite
<hw>Mel"i*lite</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>me`li</grk> honey + <ets>-lite</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧lilithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral
occurring in small yellow crystals, found in the lavas (<it>melilite
